In the light of recent events, it is high time for Sergei Lavrov, through the mouth of Maria Zakharova, to threaten with unimaginable sanctions if US troops attack Canada or, God forbid, Mexico. Then the living will certainly envy the dead (read Biden Reagan). And if suddenly Boris Johnson, riding a tank with his Minister of Defense, dares to approach the borders of sovereign Ireland, then the barbarian invasions of Ancient Rome will certainly seem like child's play when Russia punishes the henchmen of the Queen of England. And there is nothing to be silent when such events are coming ..